1. Oil-based paints are known for their smooth, even application process which can be attributed to their ease of use.
2. They often come with built-in solvents that make cleaning brushes and tools easier.
3. Oil-based paints tend to dry slowly, giving the artist more time to work with them and correct mistakes.
4. They can be easily mixed with a variety of mediums to achieve desired effects.
5. Oil-based paints can be easily cleaned up with mineral spirits or turpentine.
6. Oil-based paints do not require the use of water, which can be difficult to work with for some artists.
7. The consistency of oil-based paints makes them easy to apply with a variety of tools.